  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 240ºC/ 220ºC (fan)/ gas 9</p><p>Put a large baking tray (or two) in the oven to heat up (this will stop the pizza bottoms from going soggy!)</p><p>Add the <strong>dried yeast</strong><span class=\"text-danger\"> </span>to a large bowl with 100ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[200ml]</span> <strong>warm water </strong>and 1 tsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp] </span><strong>sugar</strong></p><p>Give it a good mix up and set aside for 5-10 min for the yeast to develop</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1595496106845-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1595496106845-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1595496106845-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1595496106845-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1595496106845-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, slice the <strong>baby plum tomatoes</strong> in half then trim the green stalk<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span><strong> </strong>off the <strong>aubergine<span class=\"text-danger\">[s] </span></strong>and slice in half lengthways, then into half-moons</p><p>Add the <strong>aubergine slices</strong> to one side of a separate baking tray (use<strong> baking paper</strong> to avoid it sticking) with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil </strong>and a generous pinch of<strong> salt</strong> and <strong>pepper </strong>and mix it all together</p><p>Add the <strong>halved</strong> <strong>baby plum tomatoes</strong> to the other side of the tray and put the tray in the oven for 8-10 min or until the aubergine has started to soften</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1595496111993-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1595496111993-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1595496111993-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1595496111993-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1595496111993-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, peel and finely chop (or grate) the <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Add the <strong>tomato paste</strong> to a bowl with the <strong>chopped garlic</strong> and a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong>, <strong>pepper</strong> and<strong> sugar</strong></p><p>Add 4 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[8 tbsp] </span><strong>cold water</strong> and stir it all together – this is your <strong>tomato sauce</strong></p><p>Drain and pat the <strong>mozzarella</strong> dry with kitchen paper<strong> </strong>(squeeze as much liquid out as you can!)</p><p>Tear the <strong>drained mozzarella</strong> into rough, bite-sized pieces</p>",
