            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1595496139934-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Repeat this process for the next pizza base<span class=\"text-danger\">[s] </span>(make sure the pizzas don't overlap on the trays to avoid raw dough!)</p><p>Top them with the <strong>dried oregano</strong>, <strong>roasted tomatoes</strong>, <strong>torn mozzarella</strong>, <strong>roasted aubergine</strong> and <strong>half</strong> of the <strong>grated Italian hard cheese </strong>(save the rest for garnish!), then tear over<strong> </strong>the<strong> basil leaves</strong></p><p>Drizzle the crusts with <strong>olive oil</strong>, then put the tray<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span> in the oven for 12-15 min until the crust has puffed up and browned</p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
